Integration Procedures in Multiplay Subscription Management

The following reusable Vlocity Integration Procedures (VIPs) are provided in Multiplay Subscription Management.

SFI-AbstractionService
This Integration Procedure implements the abstraction framework. The abstraction framework is a blackbox service that provides an interface between the Multiplay Subscription Management product model and the core components that interact with the product model.
SFI-AccessBasedOnRoles
This Integration Procedure is used to determine if a requested action can be performed on a given account by the logged in agent or customer. If the logged in user is an agent, this Integration Procedure further checks if the customer requesting the action is permitted to make that request on that account.
SFI-ActiveAccount
This Integration Procedure is used by the eligibility framework to determine if a requested action can be performed on an account. This Integration Procedure verifies if the specified account status is active. It is called from the eligibility rules matrix.
SFI-AddDisconnectNumberFeeProduct
This Integration Procedure is used in workflows that allow a user to select a new phone number. This Integration Procedure compares a selected new number with the existing number. If the new number belongs to a different category, and if a different fee is associated with the new number category compared to the existing number category, this Integration Procedure adds an order line item for the new number category fee. If no fee is required, then this Integration Procedure updates the attributes of the selected new number in the order line item.
SFI-BasketToCartUsingCartContextKey
This Integration Procedure converts a basket to cart using cartContextKey by calling the DC API Vlocity_Cmt.CpqAppHandler.createEcomCart.
SFI-CheckEligibility
This Integration Procedure calls the eligibility framework and runs eligibility checks as per the rules specified in the eligibility matrix.
SFI-CheckValidUserType
This Integration Procedure is used by the eligibility framework to determine if a requested action can be performed by the logged in user. When the calling workflow is launched from the customer portal, this Integration Procedure verifies that the custom metadata record for the associated profile has the value Customer. When the calling workflow is launched from the agent console, this Integration Procedure verifies that the custom metadata record for the associated profile has the value Agent or Supervisor.
SFI-CreateCustomerInteractionTopic
This Integration Procedure creates an interaction topic in an OmniScript for a given customer interaction ID. The customer interaction topic that is created can be associated with an account, asset, contact, or subscription if they are provided as input to this Integration Procedure.
SFI-CreateMACDOrder
This Integration Procedure creates an order for the requested date from the specified root asset ID and account ID.
SFI-DeliveryOptionPostProcess
This Integration Procedure updates the billing and shipping address associated with an order.
SFI-GetExistingOrderDetails
This Integration Procedure gets information about existing cross orders for a specified asset ID.
SFI-GetOffersByCatalogCodeIP
This Integration Procedure uses a remote action call to CpqAppHandler to fetch offers based on the specified catalog code.
SFI-GetOrderDetails
This Integration Procedure fetches the order and order item details for a specified order ID. It is used to find and display information about existing cross orders when the cross order check indicates that a cross order exists.
SFI-GetServiceDetails
This Integration Procedure fetches the details of services whose ID is sent in ContextId input parameter.
SFI-GetServiceList
This Integration Procedure is used to get the details of services associated with an account.
SFI-GetSimCardsByStatusDemo
This demo Integration Procedure gets a list of SIM cards based on the specified status. It also updates the status of the SIM cards to reserved. This Integration Procedure is used in workflows that allow users to order a SIM card.
SFI-GetUserType
This Integration Procedure returns the name, type, and role of a user based on the specified user ID.
SFI-GetUserTypeAndBaseUrl
This Integration Procedure returns the name, type, and role of a user based on the specified user ID. It also fetches the base URL for the customer self service portal and for the agent console from the corresponding custom metadata records.
SFI-PreProcessInlifeJourney
This Integration Procedure is used to set up the inlife journey workflows. It performs various functions such as setting the context as either account or service, setting the currency symbol, getting the user type, and validating the user's eligibility to perform the requested action.
SFI-SubmitOrder
This Integration Procedure submits orders either to Order Management or to Industries CPQ depending on the mode you set for submitting orders. You can specify the mode for submitting orders in the VPL Metadata Config custom metadata. By default, the OrderSubmitMode custom metadata record specifies CPQ.
SFI-UpdateCustomerInteractionTopic
This Integration Procedure updates interaction topics in an OmniScript.
SFI-UpdateNumberInventoryOnSelectionDemo
This Integration Procedure updates the Number Inventory when, given a current selection, a user selects a different number. It updates the status of the previously selected number to Reserved and sets the status of the currently selected number to Locked.
SFI-UpdateOrderDetails
This Integration Procedure updates details of an order based on input received from the user.
